<figureCitation box="[151,284,690,716]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 1" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2" captionStartId-0="2.[151,250,1464,1488]" captionStartId-1="2.[151,250,1930,1954]" captionTargetBox-0="[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetBox-1="[152,1431,1585,1906]" captionTargetId-0="figure-28@2.[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetId-1="figure-87@2.[151,1436,1585,1906]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="2" captionText-0="FIGURE 1. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) bimacula sp. nov.. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–C. head and pronotum: B. dorsal view, C. lateral view; D. second and third abdominal tergites in lateral view; E–I. apex of abdomen: E. dorsal view, F. lateral view, G. apico-ventral view, H. apical view, I. ventral view." captionText-1="FIGURE 2. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) bimacula sp. nov.. Male: A–B. tegmina in dorsal view: A. left tegmen, B. right tegmen." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911367" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911373" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6911367/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6911373/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Figures 1–2</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="94" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,761,1904]" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,761,787]" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This new species differs from other species of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Griffini" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[807,1320,762,788]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllacrididae" genus="Metriogryllacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amitarum" subGenus="Metriogryllacris">
<emphasis box="[807,992,762,788]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Metriogryllacris</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1009,1194,762,788]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Metriogryllacris</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1211,1320,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">amitarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by: wings only reaching the middle area of fifth abdominal tergite; pronotum without black margins and longitudinal black median band, and only with 1 black spot at anterior and posterior margins respectively (
<figureCitation box="[1223,1311,834,860]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1464,1488]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetId="figure-28@2.[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) bimacula sp. nov.. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–C. head and pronotum: B. dorsal view, C. lateral view; D. second and third abdominal tergites in lateral view; E–I. apex of abdomen: E. dorsal view, F. lateral view, G. apico-ventral view, H. apical view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911367/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
); spines of male ninth abdominal tergite slender, and directing downwards and slightly outwards (
<figureCitation box="[1121,1234,870,896]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1464,1488]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetId="figure-28@2.[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) bimacula sp. nov.. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–C. head and pronotum: B. dorsal view, C. lateral view; D. second and third abdominal tergites in lateral view; E–I. apex of abdomen: E. dorsal view, F. lateral view, G. apico-ventral view, H. apical view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911367/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Fig. 1G–I</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="94" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,761,1904]" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,422,905,932]" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Body medium-sized. Frons ovoid with very fine transverse riffles and sparse punctures (
<figureCitation box="[159,249,942,968]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1464,1488]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetId="figure-28@2.[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) bimacula sp. nov.. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–C. head and pronotum: B. dorsal view, C. lateral view; D. second and third abdominal tergites in lateral view; E–I. apex of abdomen: E. dorsal view, F. lateral view, G. apico-ventral view, H. apical view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911367/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Ocelli indistinct.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,761,1904]" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">
Pronotum with anterior margin slightly projecting, posterior margin nearly straight (
<figureCitation box="[1179,1270,978,1004]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1464,1488]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetId="figure-28@2.[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) bimacula sp. nov.. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–C. head and pronotum: B. dorsal view, C. lateral view; D. second and third abdominal tergites in lateral view; E–I. apex of abdomen: E. dorsal view, F. lateral view, G. apico-ventral view, H. apical view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911367/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
); lateral lobes longer than deep, posterior margin of ventral margin slightly extending downward (
<figureCitation box="[1114,1204,1014,1040]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1464,1488]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetId="figure-28@2.[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) bimacula sp. nov.. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–C. head and pronotum: B. dorsal view, C. lateral view; D. second and third abdominal tergites in lateral view; E–I. apex of abdomen: E. dorsal view, F. lateral view, G. apico-ventral view, H. apical view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911367/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Fore coxae with 1 spine. Fore and middle femora unarmed on ventral surfaces, tibiae with 5 pairs of ventral spurs, including 1 pair of apical ones. Hind femora with 9–12 internal and 7–8 external spines on ventral surface; tibiae with 5–6 internal and 5 external spines on dorsal surface, apices with 1 pair of dorsal spurs, 1 pair of subapical ventral spurs and 2 pairs of ventral spurs. Wings short, only reaching the middle area of fifth abdominal tergite. Tegmina (
<figureCitation box="[1351,1422,1158,1184]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1930,1954]" captionTargetBox="[152,1431,1585,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-87@2.[151,1436,1585,1906]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) bimacula sp. nov.. Male: A–B. tegmina in dorsal view: A. left tegmen, B. right tegmen." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911373/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
): Radius forks into two branches near apical forth area; MA fused with R in basal forth area, then raised from R; in the left tegmen (
<figureCitation box="[340,430,1230,1256]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1930,1954]" captionTargetBox="[152,1431,1585,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-87@2.[151,1436,1585,1906]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) bimacula sp. nov.. Male: A–B. tegmina in dorsal view: A. left tegmen, B. right tegmen." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911373/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
) MP and CuA free at base but fused with each other in subbasal area for about one cell length, then suddenly separated, then MP fused with MA in short distance and again separated, then MP and CuA free, undivided; while in right tegmen (
<figureCitation box="[588,673,1302,1328]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1930,1954]" captionTargetBox="[152,1431,1585,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-87@2.[151,1436,1585,1906]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) bimacula sp. nov.. Male: A–B. tegmina in dorsal view: A. left tegmen, B. right tegmen." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911373/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
) MP and CuA fused in basal area, undivided. Both tegmina: Cubitus posterior undivided, free throughout; with 3 anal veins.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,761,1904]" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">
Abdominal tergites two and three each with two rows of stridulatory pegs (
<figureCitation box="[1046,1136,1374,1400]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1464,1488]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetId="figure-28@2.[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) bimacula sp. nov.. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–C. head and pronotum: B. dorsal view, C. lateral view; D. second and third abdominal tergites in lateral view; E–I. apex of abdomen: E. dorsal view, F. lateral view, G. apico-ventral view, H. apical view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911367/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Eighth abdominal tergite prolonged downwards (
<figureCitation box="[413,528,1410,1436]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1464,1488]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetId="figure-28@2.[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) bimacula sp. nov.. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–C. head and pronotum: B. dorsal view, C. lateral view; D. second and third abdominal tergites in lateral view; E–I. apex of abdomen: E. dorsal view, F. lateral view, G. apico-ventral view, H. apical view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911367/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Fig. 1E–F</figureCitation>
). Ninth abdominal tergite semi-globular, ventral margin with 1 pair of small spines in the middle which directing downwards and slightly outwards (
<figureCitation box="[893,1019,1446,1472]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1464,1488]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetId="figure-28@2.[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) bimacula sp. nov.. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–C. head and pronotum: B. dorsal view, C. lateral view; D. second and third abdominal tergites in lateral view; E–I. apex of abdomen: E. dorsal view, F. lateral view, G. apico-ventral view, H. apical view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911367/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Fig. 1G–H</figureCitation>
). Cerci short and slender. Subgenital plate basally broad, apical area trapezoidal projected in the middle, posterior margin with a shallowly concavity in the middle (
<figureCitation box="[285,362,1518,1544]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1464,1488]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetId="figure-28@2.[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) bimacula sp. nov.. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–C. head and pronotum: B. dorsal view, C. lateral view; D. second and third abdominal tergites in lateral view; E–I. apex of abdomen: E. dorsal view, F. lateral view, G. apico-ventral view, H. apical view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911367/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Fig. 1I</figureCitation>
); long styli inserted at the lateral constriction (
<figureCitation box="[886,962,1518,1544]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1464,1488]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetId="figure-28@2.[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) bimacula sp. nov.. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–C. head and pronotum: B. dorsal view, C. lateral view; D. second and third abdominal tergites in lateral view; E–I. apex of abdomen: E. dorsal view, F. lateral view, G. apico-ventral view, H. apical view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911367/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Fig. 1I</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,761,1904]" box="[199,418,1554,1580]" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1554,1580]" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,761,1904]" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1589,1615]" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Coloration.</emphasis>
General color yellow brown, face uniformly yellowish brown (
<figureCitation box="[1070,1162,1590,1616]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1464,1488]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetId="figure-28@2.[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) bimacula sp. nov.. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–C. head and pronotum: B. dorsal view, C. lateral view; D. second and third abdominal tergites in lateral view; E–I. apex of abdomen: E. dorsal view, F. lateral view, G. apico-ventral view, H. apical view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911367/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Pronotum with brown margins, disc with 1 black spot at anterior and posterior margin respectively (
<figureCitation box="[1020,1142,1626,1652]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1464,1488]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetId="figure-28@2.[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) bimacula sp. nov.. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–C. head and pronotum: B. dorsal view, C. lateral view; D. second and third abdominal tergites in lateral view; E–I. apex of abdomen: E. dorsal view, F. lateral view, G. apico-ventral view, H. apical view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911367/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Fig. 1B–C</figureCitation>
). Tegmina brown (
<figureCitation box="[1353,1423,1626,1652]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1930,1954]" captionTargetBox="[152,1431,1585,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-87@2.[151,1436,1585,1906]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) bimacula sp. nov.. Male: A–B. tegmina in dorsal view: A. left tegmen, B. right tegmen." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911373/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Ventral surface of hind femora brownish. From fifth to ninth abdominal tergites with large black spots on dorsal surfaces (
<figureCitation box="[258,375,1698,1724]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1464,1488]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetId="figure-28@2.[154,1434,181,1441]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) bimacula sp. nov.. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–C. head and pronotum: B. dorsal view, C. lateral view; D. second and third abdominal tergites in lateral view; E–I. apex of abdomen: E. dorsal view, F. lateral view, G. apico-ventral view, H. apical view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911367/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Fig. 1E–F</figureCitation>
); spines of male ninth abdominal tergite brown.
</paragraph>
